  "abstract": "ICGV 87165, a high-yielding peanut (Arachis hypogaea L. subsp.\r\nhypogaea var. hypogaea) germplasm line (Reg. no. GP-78, P1\r\n594923) with multiple disease and insect resistance, was released\r\nin 1994 by the Plant Materials Identification Committee of the\r\nInternational Crops Research Institute for the Semi-Arid Tropics\r\n(ICRISAT) because of its resistance to rust (caused by Puccinia\r\narachidis Speg.) and late leaf spot [caused by Phaeoisariopsis personata\r\n(Berk. & Curt.) Arx], and moderate resistance to bacterial\r\nwilt [caused by Pseudomonas solanacearum (Smith) Smith], leaf\r\nminer (Aproarema modicella Deventar), and tobacco caterpillar\r\n[Spodoptera litura (F.)].",
